US rapper Cardi B arrives for Rihanna's 5th Annual Diamond Ball Benefitting The Clara Lionel Foundation at Cipriani Wall Street on September 12, 2019 in New York City. JOHANNESBURG - US rapper Cardi B is expected to perform in South Africa in June. The I Like It hitmaker will headline the Castle Lite Unlocked concert at the Ticketpro Dome in Johannesburg. READ: Bonnie Mbuli set to star in international drama series "Guess what? We’re bringing@iamcardib to #CastleLiteUnlocks! S/o to you if you copped your Early Bird tickets today, now you can thank yourself!", Castle Lite said on Twitter. Official tickets for the concert go on sale on Friday and are available at castlelite.co.za. Social media went into a frenzy on Thursday following the announcement of her performance.